-- CTC Media’s CTC TV Falls to Sixth Place, TNS-Global Says
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-07-13T17:33:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-13/ctc-media-s-ctc-tv-falls-to-sixth-place-tns-global-says.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s CTC television
channel fell to the sixth most-watched among Russian viewers 18
years and older in the week to July 8, from fifth a week before,
according to TNS-Global.  Viewer share for CTC TV, the Nasdaq-listed Russian media
company’s biggest source of revenue, was unchanged at 5.5
percent in the week to July 8, while rival REN TV’s share rose
to 5.9 percent from 5.4 percent in the previous week, pushing it
ahead of CTC to the fifth most watched in the country, data
researcher TNS-Global said by e-mail today.  CTC’s average daily audience among viewers 4 years old and
over fell to 5.9 percent from 6.2 percent in the week to July 1,
the data show. CTC remained in fifth place among viewers 4 years
old and over, TNS-Global said.  Russia’s NTV Television was the most watched among both
audience categories. Government-controlled Pervyi Kanal was the
second-most watched in both segments, pushing Rossiya-1 to the
third most watched in both categories and TNT TV was fourth, the
data show.  To contact the reporters on this story:
